{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_hawthorne_ver01/data/sn84026749/00205698267/1938021501/0203.xml":{"full_text":"JAPAN PROPOSES\nARMS CUT\u2014FOR U. S.\nNEWS BEHIND THE NEWS\nBy PAXIL MALLON\n(World Copyright, 1938. by King Feature* Syndicate, Inc, All Righta\nReserved. Reproduction in Full or in Part Strictly Prohibited.)\nTHE not-verv-subtle disarmament proposal in the Japa\nnese note shows the inside and outside .of the world\nsituation.\nThe Japanese proposed aboli\ntion of capital ships in words\nwringing wet with tears because\nthe same\n\u2022\u2018earnest\u201d sug\ngestion had\n\u201cunfortunate\nly\u201d been turn\ned down by\nthe United\nStates and\nBritain at the\nLondon di s\na r m a m e nt\ncons erence.\nThe real\ndepth of earn\nestness in the\nsuggestion is\nevidenced by\nthe compara-\nPaul Mallon\ntive naval figures which show:\nCapital ships\u2014U. S. 15, Japan\n10.\nCruisers\u2014U. S. 27, Japan 26.\nDestroyers\u2014U. S. 35, Japan\n67.\nSubmarines \u2014U. S. 22, Japan\n<l.\nIn other words, Japan eau\nnestly proposes disarmament\nfor the United States. Her plan\nsimply is to establish Japanese\nsuperiority by having the U. S.\nand Britain abolish expensive\nlarge ships in which they are\nsuperior.\n\"Unfortunately,\u201d as the Japa\nnese say, other secondary na\ntions are similarly earnest foe\nthe same kind of disarmament\n\u2014for the other fellow. The\nstatesmanship of the world is\nincapable of working out any\nsolution except maximum self\ndefense.\nThis need not mean war but\ncertainly means financial col\nlapse for those least able to af\nford the. expensive game.\nTHE genera? idea that the Ad\nministration is stalling for\ntime, h .ping for an early sum\nmer business revival, seems to\nbe just a logical assumption, but\nnot a policy. That is, those of\nficials whc are closest to the\nExecutive chair have never\nheard such a suggestion made,\nbut believe things may naturally\nwork out that way.\nReal reason so little is being\ndone by the Government is that\nmost of the publicly discussed\nplans are not favored on high in\ntheir present form.\nA very minor rabbit is due to\nemerge from the Treasury cha\npeau shortly. Also the rail de\ncision will be out before March\n1. Something will be done about\neasing loans for small business,\nbut there is much quarreling on\nthe inside about the method of\ndoing it. Nothing has developed\nin the housing program to war\nrant any great expectations\nfor it.\nGeneral inside outlook here\nfavors a good early summer pick\nup, a fall dependent largely on\ncrops, and then what the ex\nperts are beginning to call an\n\u201caverage\u201d year, meaning neither\ngood nor bad.\nTHIS VINSON proposal for a\nCongressional declaration of\nnaval protection policy bears\nthe wrong name.\nAs House Naval Chairman\n'Likker'\nCoast Scents Kind\nBay State Drinks\nSACRAMENTO, Cal.. Feb. 15\n(1.N.5.) .\u2014United States Commis\nsioner John-Q; Brown is thinking\nof starting an investigation into\nwhat kind of liquor they drink in\nMassachusetts.\n\u201cI want to be sure and avoid\nany of it,\u201d the commissioner said,\nafter holding a preliminary hear\ning in the case of Tuano W. Neu\nvonen. 22, of Gardner, Mass., who\nis charged with stealing an auto\nmobile in that city and driving\nit to California.\n\u201cI got drunk on whiskey,\u201d the\nyouth told Brown, \"and the next\nthing I knew I was in California\nand driving a strange car. Every\nthing is blank.\u201d\n\u201cSome whiskey,\u201d Brown com\nmented as he ordered Neuvonen\nheld to answer and placed him\nunder $2,500 bail.\nJones to Lecture\nOn West\u2019s Beauties\nALEXANDRIA, Va., Feb. 15.\nAn illustrated lecture on the\n\u201cUtah Arizona Wonderlands\u201d by\nRand-ill Jones representatives of.\nthe Union Pacific railroad, was\nto feature the weekly meeting of\nine Alexandria Rotary Club today.\nJones wiil repeat his camera\nlecture on the Zion and Bryce\nCanyon National Parks for stu\ndents of the George Washington\nHigh Scnool February 24.\nFor\nHOME DELIVERY\nof Herald and Times\nBy\nPersonally Guaranteed\nCARRIER SERVICE\nPhon.\nREpublic 1234\nAck far \u201cCirculation\u2019*\n7*\u00abZ\u00abpAana REpublie 1234\nVinson called at the White\nHouse a few days before making\nhis proposal, the general as\nsumption is he received some\nhelp on it from the President.\nAs a matter of fact, certain\nother more conclusive inside\nevidence indicates it was partly\ncomposed in the State Depart\nment by that master of diplo\nmatic wording, State Secretary\nHull.\nNavy tacticians say it means\nnothing. They characterize it as\na political maneuver to flank\nthe congressional opposition.\nThe supposedly clever idea be\nhind it is to make clear that\nif Congress wants to protect\nboth coasts and yet not have a\nnaval understanding with Brit\nain. it must provide a Navy\nmuch larger than Mr. Roose\nvelt has proposed\u2014in fact, one\nabout twice the size of the pres\nent Navy. It must have another\nfleet for the Atlantic.\nIT may not turn out to be as\nintended.\nAdmirr\u2019 Leahy testified Jan\nuary 30: \u201cThe proposed in\ncrease is not sufficient to guard\nagainst an attack on both\nshores at once.\u201d\nPrimary purpose mentioned\nin the proposed declaration of\npolicy is for a Navy \"of suffi\ncient strength to guard the con\ntinental United States by af\nfording necessary protection to\nthe coast line in both oceans\nat one and the same time.\u201d\nThus it seems to pledge Con\ngress to inestimable future\nbuilding beyond the increases\nnow being debated. In other\nwords, it sounds like a trick to\nget Congress on record for a\nNavy far bigger than the wild\nest dream of the wildest ad\nmiral.\nActually there seems solid\nground for believing the Ad\nministration has no such inten\ntion, but the crafty words may\nbe bent double for boomerang\nuse by the opposition.\n.'act is both sides are avoid\ning frankness for theiecwn pur\nposes.\nNote\u2014Despite the confusion,\nthe Roosevelt program will go\nthrough, and\u2014mark this well\u2014\nmany of the leaders now trying\nto smoke the Administration\nout into a frank posi ion, will\nvote for it in the end.\nDEBATE in Congress over what\nships are offensive probably\nis an endless argument.\nThe Japanese note sought to\ncontribute to this argument by\ncharacterizing capital ships and\nairplane carriers as \u201cthe only\u201d\noffensive type of ships.\nWorld War experience showed\nthe only offensive weapon of\nmuch consequence on the seas\nthen was the submarine. Both\nBritish and German fleets then\nwere so determined to defend\ntheir respective coastlines\nagainst each other that they\ndid not generally dare to risk\nlosses by encountering each\nother.\nTHE Senate economy bloc has\ndecided definitely to stay\nout of the argument over an ad\nditional $250,000,000 of relief\nfunds for Mr. Roosevelt. The\nByrnes committee study has con\nvinced the economy crowd a de\nficiency appropriation really was\nnecessary. They will go ahead\nwith hearings soon to work out\na permanent relief plan in con\nnection with the coming relief\nappropriation for next year.\nCongressional talk is that per\nhaps two billions will be needed\nnext year, but it is only talk.\nOnly basis for it is that at the\npresent rate of expenditure for\nWPA, two billions would be\nneeded.\nJLmiDSJh\nRub it on lhe chest, 111\nInsert it in the nose; 111\n111 Using Mentholatum\n111 Discomfort quickly goes,\n-f\u00bb wearer A oj\"\nso-a r\nlimited, time <*nuf\nThousands who wear dental plates\nknow FABTEETH to be a pleasant aid\nfor all day comfort.and security of fit.\nAnyope who wears a plate or bridge is\ninvited, at our expense, to try KLEEN\nTEETH for cleaning plates or bridges.\nNo daily brushing \u2014no acid \u2014no harm.\nKLEENTEETH easily and quickly re\nmoves sticky film stains tarnish and\nfood debris that causes \u201cplate taste\"\nand \u201cdenture breath.\u201d Simply soak plate\nin solution of KLEENTEETH.\nGet your package of\nFASTEETH today and a M\ntrial package of KLEEN\nTEETH at no added cost.\n\u25b2ll druggists. I J\nday trial package I A\n<f KLEENTEETH\nwUhtachpunhaie\n\nLAGUARDIA ACTS\nIN FUR STRIKE\nNEW YORK, Feb. 15 (1.N.5.).\nMayor LaGuardia today was to\nattempt to end the combination\nlockout and strike in the fur in\ndustry. which went into effect\nhere yesterday.\nNegotiations between the Inter\nnational Fur Workers Union and\nthe Associated Fur Coat and Trim\nming Manufacturers for a re\nnewal of their agreement, which\nexpired January 31, have been\ndeadlocked.\nUnion leaders maintained only\n1,800 workers in 110 shops were\naffected by the lockout, while\nspokesmen for the employers es\ntimated about 400 firms had\nclosed their plants.\nMONEY-RAVER I\nMl A JEIAkB I\na. y '-<Z.. vfl fl\n\nAir\" gOAWTiTiES LIMITED\u2014NONE SOLD TO DEALERSj '7 9\nI M I<th i PA. AVE. N.W. 17th PA. AVE. N.W. 14th i COL. RD. N.W. B\nIft Barver R 11th J PA. AVE. N.W. 13th H STS. N.W. 18th A COL. RO. N.W. f dayai 1\nH POCKET COMB, j' 9th 4 F STS W j 4th SHSTS o< 12 th&GSTS. N.W. I taatm rpiku\nI MIRROR and 9 fl S TOOTH BRUSH 9\nNAU FILE SIT J LORELEI I\nI J In.Laatharetta Cosa M99RflHHHfl9fl99flflfllHHfl|M TOOTH PASTE\nx 10c' value W S M Both For- i I\nwith It Ufl Phillips'Tooth Paste 23 c B 1 this 1 Sc 1 5 I\nTHIS COUPOH fl with tree bonbon dish GS COUPON V I\nB Midol Tablets 50c Size 2<* 11 I\nI CZumhml l rbasol B,usble I g assorto\" j\nI SHOETREES 31 J e L I |JERGENS|\nFor Every Member of I B StCF mA A R i\nthe Family CreaiHS 55c Size 25 c |fl I JWMr g\n9 WITH THIS J Jfl w lh shit |K\ncoupon 5 H Watkins Shampoo 50c Size 35c H M p\u00ab pon only\nPAIR.... fl Scare A f\nRubbi g Alcohol pi-t 7c\na Styptic Pencils ]c fl \u25a0fl\u2019\u2019\nI I\nB Hospital Cotton 1-ib. JQc B Sk JB\nI COIN POPPE! I Aspirin Tablets Bottle. OH 001 Ac B chocolate\nYou can have hot and tasty fl P \u25a0O C COVERED CHERRIES\npopcorn when- H _ Fresh picked cherries dip-\nI ever you want it. WJC TumS 10e Size O for llC fl ped in rich, fine-\nTide Safe ONLY fl X II 6 ly- milled choco- OQc\nMIOGIT POPCORN, t Be fl t D Ute< Full Pound Lg\n\u25a0|l J| fl Ipana Tooth Paste 50c Size 2JC J\nI B Lighthouse Cleanser 2 C B\nI I I IB Menthol Inhalers 10c Size I I\nJ Bromo Seltzer 60e Size 34c 11 K\nevelyn gay Seidlitz Powders 12. |]c salon bath crystals\nHAND LOTION Perfumes ind softens water. II\nAlmond Benzoin, or it. e- m aa. fl Money back if not satisfied.\nAlmond Rose 9 Nujol Pint 75c Size 45c pA\nI I I WE 59*\nI I Suppositories 12. 16c 11 Lttz ZZ.\nI I I Phillips Milk of\n-H B Magnesia 50c Size 29c|l B W I\nI Boric Acid 8-oz. 9c|| K Xjl\nA\ntotforJ;^,m.?r.S 2 I Quinine 30c Size 17c CIOTHIS AND HAT BRUSH\nreproductions of mm A Ideal for home or office; has\nfamous paintings. QQ( same type bristlesas\nFOR ONLY .v 70 fl Be-Co Ammonia Oc higher-priced ones. lUc\nI ODORONO Regular B Per de Pin I LIFEBUOY SOAP\n9 and Instant O2c B Carter\u2019s Pills 25. 14c I Limit 2to a 2^. or 9\n35c Size Customer C\nI |S C .N S LOTION I I COLO I\n50c Size Ji c S DUST\nTHE WASHINGTON TIMES, TUESDAY, FEBRUARY 15, 1935\nSupport for McNutt Doubted\nBy EARL GODWIN\nPoliticians who are waiting with\ninterest the 4,000-man reception\nto be held In Washington Feb\nruary 23 for Commissioner Gen\neral Paul V. McNutt, of the Phil\nippines, say the commissioner has\nbeen stating he would someday\nbe president of the United States\n\u201cever since he was out of the\ncradle.\u201d\nThe reception is presumably to\nbe a gathering together of as\nmany men who can corral Demo\ncratic national convention dele\ngates as possible. The fact that\nPaul V. McNutt is running for the\nPresidency is no secret: the excit\ning thing to learn is whether or\nnot he will be able to collect any\nthing while here which looks like\nan okay from the White House\nor from Chairman James Farley\nof the Democratic national com\nmittee.\nHe probably will not even get\nas much as a four-leaf clover from\neither the White House lawn or\nthe little strip of greensward\naround the Post Office Building\nwhere Chairman Farley spends\nsome of his time\u2014a strip of greens\nward planted by one of Senator\n\u201cJoe\u201d Guffey\u2019s Democratic land\nscaping constitutents.\nPaul McNutt, having filled a\nsingle term as Indiana's governor,\nafter being Commander of the\nAmerican Legion,, was sent to the\npolitical left field\u2014the Philip\npines, none the less! But he served\nnotice before he went that it was\ntoo far away from Indiana and\nthat he would come back in about\na year.\nVISIT OVERDUE\nAnd so he comes: a little over\ndue, possibly, but someone has\ncasually arranged a whirlwind\ncampaign of speeches and appear\nances. culminating with tn e\nmassed reception here in Washing\nton. Anyone in the United States\nwho dosn\u2019t know Paul McNutt at\nthe end of that series is possibly\nsomeone who doesn\u2019t read the\npapers, listen to the radio or at\ntend the movies.\nIt should be known that the\nIndiana political machine is\nworking effectively: even more so\nthan in the old GOP days. The\nMcNutt dynasty is still able to\n1 pick \u2019em whenever needed. The\nMcNutt machine put over M.\nj Clifford Townsend for governor,\nafter Governor McNutt left and\nchose his own lieutenant governor\nto succeed him at the State house.\nIt developed and elected Sherman\nMinton, now U. S. Senator from!\nthat State.\nMONEY POURS IN\nPaul McNutt fashioned sena- j\ntonial timber out of Minton's prow- i\ness as public defender for the'\npeople against the utilities. It is!\ncommon talk here that Senator j\nVan Nuys would have to get a\nMcNutt okay for a successful cam\npaign, renomination and re-elec-j\ntion. All in all. the Indiana view\nis that McNutt is ace high ini\npolitics.\nTelephone REpublie 1234\n/J LOW 2 I F 1\n\u25a0mmUl prices \u25a0omm\nI Prictt for the District of Columbia until the eloeo of Bueineee I\nWodnoeday, February 16, 1938.\nJUMBO BUTTER -35 c\nSANITARY\u2019S BUTTER.. >37c I\nI LAND O'LAKE